How to deploy images that are not available on my drive?

1. If you want to import and deploy images that are not available on my drive, you will first need to download the required `.ova` file from the internet and convert it into `.qcow2` format. If you are able to get the `.qcow2` file directly, that is even better. A good starting point to search for the required image is: `https://drive.labhub.eu.org/`

2. To convert the `.ova` file, first upload or paste it into the `/opt/unetlab/temp` folder on your PNETLab VM.

3. Open the CLI on the PNETLab VM and run:
   `cd /opt/unetlab/temp`
   Then run:
   `ls`
   Make sure the `.ova` file is visible in this directory before proceeding.

4. Extract the `.ova` file by running:
   `tar -xvf yourfile.ova`
   This will extract the contents of the `.ova` file and give you a `.vmdk` disk file.

5. Locate the extracted `.vmdk` file in the same folder. Then convert it into `.qcow2` format by running:
   `qemu-img convert -f vmdk -O qcow2 yourfilein.vmdk virtioa.qcow2`
   Make sure to use a capital `O` in `-O qcow2`.

6. Once the `.qcow2` file is created, follow the naming guide here:
   `https://www.eve-ng.net/index.php/documentation/qemu-image-namings/`
   Rename the `.qcow2` file according to the vendor and platform requirements given in that guide. In most cases, correctly renaming the file is enough.

7. Now go to the following directory:
   `/opt/unetlab/addons/qemu`

8. Create a new folder for the image. The folder name is very important and must match the expected naming format for that product.

9. To find the correct folder name for your specific vendor or product image, refer to:
   `https://www.eve-ng.net/index.php/documentation/howtos/`

10. Place the renamed `.qcow2` file inside the correct folder under `/opt/unetlab/addons/qemu`.

11. After copying the file, you can delete the temporary extracted files from `/opt/unetlab/temp` if you no longer need them.

12. Refresh PNETLab and check the node list. The image should now be available as a deployable node.

